      <section>
         <title>The Components in the UPS Principle Diagram</title>
         <table pgwide="1">
            <tgroup cols="3">
               <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="9.99%"/>
               <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="29.72%"/>
               <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="41.00*"/>
               <thead>
                  <row>
                     <entry valign="top"/>
                     <entry valign="top">Component</entry>
                     <entry valign="top">Explanation</entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>X001</entry>
                     <entry>Rectifier mains terminal</entry>
                     <entry>This terminal provides for the connection of the rectifier
mains (L1, L2, L3, PE).</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>T001</entry>
                     <entry>Option: Rectifier mains transfomer</entry>
                     <entry>Matches the rectifier mains voltage to the correct value for
the rectifier, and provides galvanic isolation.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Q001</entry>
                     <entry>Rectifier mains
input switch</entry>
                     <entry>This switch ensures
isolation of the rectifier mains input (no trip function).</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>K101</entry>
                     <entry>Input
backfeed contactor</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Power_Connection_Board_A101_REF_0000103189.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A101</entry>
                     <entry>Power connection
board</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Power_Connection_Board_A101_REF_0000103189.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A102</entry>
                     <entry>Controller box</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Controller_Box_A102_REF_0000103188.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>T101 — T102</entry>
                     <entry>Power modules</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Power_Module_T101_T102_REF_0000102069.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>X201</entry>
                     <entry>Battery terminal</entry>
                     <entry>This terminal ensures the connection of the battery positive
pole (B+) and the negative pole (B-).</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Q201</entry>
                     <entry>Battery switch</entry>
                     <entry/>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Q401</entry>
                     <entry>Static bypass switch (Thyristors)</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Static_Bypass_Switch_Module_SBS_REF_0000103119.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A401</entry>
                     <entry>Static bypass switch controller</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_SBS_Controller_A401_REF_0000103064.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>T401</entry>
                     <entry>Option: Inverter output transformer</entry>
                     <entry>This transformer galvanically isolates the load from the battery
and adapts the output voltage to the required voltage of the inverter
power module. No transformer is used, if no galvanic isolation is
required, and if the required output voltage is in the range from
380–415 V for 3–phase system and 220–240 V for
1–phase systems.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>X501</entry>
                     <entry>Bypass mains input terminal</entry>
                     <entry>This terminal provides for the connection of the bypass mains:
1, 2, or 3 phases, neutral and ground, dependent on the configuration
and type. For 3–phase systems one common set of terminals for
rectifier and bypass mains is possible.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Q501</entry>
                     <entry>Bypass mains input switch</entry>
                     <entry>This switch isolates the bypass mains input.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>T501</entry>
                     <entry>Option: Bypass
mains input transformer</entry>
                     <entry>This component
provides for the galvanic isolation between the bypass mains input
and the load. It can also be installed in the case of a different
bypass mains input voltage and output voltage. A stabilizer can be
installed instead of a transformer.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Q528</entry>
                     <entry>Bypass
mains input switch</entry>
                     <entry>Provides
for the isolation of the bypass static switch input.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Q601</entry>
                     <entry>Manual
bypass switch (MBS)</entry>
                     <entry>This
switch enables service or maintenance work. Two positions are available:<ul>
                           <li>
                              <p>Auto: in this position the load is supplied from the
system (inverter or static bypass)</p>
                           </li>
                           <li>
                              <p>Bypass: in this position the load is supplied directly
from the bypass mains. The static switch is isolated from the bypass
mains. For a total isolation of the system part, Q001 and Q201 must
also be open.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>X601</entry>
                     <entry>System
output terminal (Load terminal)</entry>
                     <entry>This
terminal provides for the connection of the load.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A801</entry>
                     <entry>Interface
board</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Interface_Board_A801_REF_0000116986.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A802,A803</entry>
                     <entry>Current
sense boards</entry>
                     <entry>These
boards contain the burden resistor for the appropriate current transformer.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A805,A806</entry>
                     <entry>Voltage
sense boards</entry>
                     <entry>These
boards convert the acquired voltage via the interface board to a standard
value.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A810</entry>
                     <entry>Human
Machine Interface (HMI)</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Human_Machine_Interface_A810_REF_0000117151.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A811</entry>
                     <entry>External
connection board</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_External_Connection_Board_A811_REF_0000103066.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A812</entry>
                     <entry>Option:
Parallel connection board</entry>
                     <entry>This
board is installed if two units are connected in parallel. The board’s
functions are:<ul>
                           <li>
                              <p>Communication between the individual units</p>
                           </li>
                           <li>
                              <p>Load sharing between the individual units. Each unit takes
over the same proportional part of the load.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>E101E102E401E701</entry>
                     <entry>Fan
system</entry>
                     <entry>Consists
of:<ul>
                           <li>
                              <p>fans with internal hall sensor for monitoring of the rotation
speed</p>
                           </li>
                           <li>
                              <p>fan monitor for monitoring the rotation speed of each fan.
If the rotation speed falls below the threshold value an alarm is
generated</p>
                           </li>
                        </ul>See <xref href="Service_Power_Module_Ventilation_E101___E701_REF_0000103117.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/> and <xref href="Service_SBS_Ventilation_E401_REF_0000103065.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>A103A104</entry>
                     <entry>Capacitor boards</entry>
                     <entry>See <xref href="Service_Capacitor_Board_A103___A104_REF_0000103190.xml"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </section>
